PRETORIA – A spirited bid by South African Police Services (SAPS) crime intelligence officer, Morris Tshabalala, popularly known as Captain KGB, to be released on bail failed in the Specialised Commercial Crime Court in Pretoria on Friday morning. READ: Police crime intelligence operative arrested by IPID Presiding over Tshabalala's bail bid, Magistrate Nicca Setshogoe ruled that the controversial police officer had failed to prove that the interest of justice permits for his release. Tshabalala faces charges including theft and defrauding the secret slush fund of the SAPS crime intelligence unit of more than R500,000. African News Agency